ERP (Enterprise Resource Planning) is a system used to manage and integrate a company's core business processes.
It collects data from departments such as finance, human resources, inventory, sales, and production.
In data analysis, ERP data helps businesses monitor operations and improve efficiency.
It is used to track resources, costs, inventory levels, and business performance.
ERP analysis supports better planning, budgeting, and decision-making across departments.
It helps organizations reduce costs, streamline processes, and improve overall productivity.
